\begin{align} x\frac{dy}{dx}&=\frac{dY}{dt}\\  (x^2)y'' &= \frac{d^2Y}{dt^2}-\frac{dY}{dt} \end{align} 
\frac{dx}{dt} = x.
Y(x(t))
\frac{dY}{dt} = \frac{dy}{dx}\frac{dx}{dt} = x \frac{dy}{dx}.
